         <abstract>
            <p>We determine all nonquadratic imaginary cyclic number fields K of 2-power degrees with ideal class groups of exponents ≤ 2, i.e., with ideal class groups such that the square of each ideal class is the principal class, i.e., such that the ideal class groups are isomorphic to some (Z/2Z)&lt;sup&gt;m&lt;/sup&gt;, m ≥ 0. There are 38 such number fields: 33 of them are quartic ones (see Theorem 13), 4 of them are octic ones (see Theorem 12), and 1 of them has degree 16 (see Theorem 11).</p>
          </abstract>
